Class SpaceBag

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.parkinggarage.model.spaces.SpaceBag
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class SpaceBag
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    A SpaceBag contains the priority queues of the different types of spaces in the garage as well as the prices designated by the manager.

      • getClosestSpace

        public Space getClosestSpace(Vehicle vehicle,
                             java.lang.String option)
        Returns the closest space in the garage for the given vehicle.
        Parameters:
        vehicle - the vehicle that we're trying to find a space for
        option - gives an option for peek or poll
        Returns:
        the smallest and closest space in the garge, null if there aren't any

      • generateSpaces

        public void generateSpaces(int totalMotorcycleSpaces,
                           int totalCarSpaces,
                           int totalTruckSpaces)
        Fills the queues with the desired amount of each space. Motorcycle spaces are placed in the front, car spaces are placed after, and truck spaces at the end.
        Parameters:
        totalMotorcycleSpaces - the desired amount of motorcycle spaces
        totalCarSpaces - the desired amount of car spaces
        totalTruckSpaces - the desired amount of truck spaces
